  <participating-org role="4" type="10">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PMU Programme Management Unit MARD</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Project Management Unit (PMU) is established under the project owner, MARD, the Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development, in Vietnam, to ensure efficient and effective project implementation of the &quot;Cooperation to strengthen the sustainable cocoa development in Vietnam&quot;, a Public Private Partnership on Cocoa. The main functions and responsibilities of the PMU are:
- Coordination of the annual planning process resulting in the project YPO using the result-based planning format;
-  Setting-up and running of the necessary monitoring systems, including activity monitoring and outcome monitoring;
- Providing technical assistance (through coaching and training) to the implementing partners in research, extension services, market support, quality improvement, policy support to ensure achieving the set outcomes and outputs in the Logframe;
- Providing quality assurance of project interventions and outputs according to SC requirements;
- Management, facilitation and supervision of consultants engaged for project related activities;
- Compilation and consolidation of the mandatory semi-annual and annual physical and financial progress reports
- Organization and facilitation of the Annual Progress Review (APR) in the province and with the respectiveimplementing agencies involved in the project components
- Management of the project budget and bank account, inclusive timely and comprehensive submission of accounts to SC;
- Preparation of the SC meetings.</narrative>
